"title": "2012: Jesus Christ, authority of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2012: jesus christ, authority of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The right of Jesus Christ to speak and act on his Father's behalf in forgiving sin, pronouncing judgment and promising eternal life to those who believe in him.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's authority underlines his divine status</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:58\">JHN 8:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:24\">1CO 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:10\">COL 2:10</a></p>\n<h2>The origin of Jesus Christ's authority</h2>\n<h3>It is given by God the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:22\">LUK 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:26-John5:27\">JHN 5:26–5:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:16\">JHN 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:18\">JHN 10:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:49-John12:50\">JHN 12:49–12:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:2\">JHN 17:2</a></p>\n<h3>It is limited by the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:40\">MRK 10:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32\">MRK 13:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:6–2:8</a></p>\n<h3>It is questioned by others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:24-Matt12:28\">MAT 12:24–12:28</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:22-Mark3:26\">MRK 3:22–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:15-Luke11:20\">LUK 11:15–11:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:23-Matt21:27\">MAT 21:23–21:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:27-Mark11:33\">MRK 11:27–11:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:1-Luke20:8\">LUK 20:1–20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:18\">JHN 2:18</a></p>\n<h2>The authority of Jesus Christ is seen in his works</h2>\n<h3>He has authority over nature</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:23-Matt8:27\">MAT 8:23–8:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:36-Mark4:41\">MRK 4:36–4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:22-Luke8:25\">LUK 8:22–8:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:22-Matt14:33\">MAT 14:22–14:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:45-Mark6:51\">MRK 6:45–6:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:15-John6:21\">JHN 6:15–6:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:18-Matt21:22\">MAT 21:18–21:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12-Mark11:14\">MRK 11:12–11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:20-Mark11:24\">MRK 11:20–11:24</a></p>\n<h3>He has authority over sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:1-Matt9:8\">MAT 9:1–9:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:3-Mark2:12\">MRK 2:3–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:18-Luke5:26\">LUK 5:18–5:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:37-Luke7:38\">LUK 7:37–7:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44-Luke7:50\">LUK 7:44–7:50</a></p>\n<h3>He has authority over sickness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:14-Matt8:15\">MAT 8:14–8:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:30-Mark1:31\">MRK 1:30–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:38-Luke4:39\">LUK 4:38–4:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:29-Matt20:34\">MAT 20:29–20:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:46-Mark10:52\">MRK 10:46–10:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:35-Luke18:43\">LUK 18:35–18:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:16\">ACT 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:30\">ACT 4:30</a></p>\n<h3>He has authority over evil</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:23-Mark1:27\">MRK 1:23–1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:33-Luke4:36\">LUK 4:33–4:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17\">LUK 10:17</a></p>\n<h3>He has authority over death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:18-Matt9:25\">MAT 9:18–9:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:22-Mark5:42\">MRK 5:22–5:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:40-Luke8:55\">LUK 8:40–8:55</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:1-Matt28:7\">MAT 28:1–28:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:1-Mark16:6\">MRK 16:1–16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1-Luke24:8\">LUK 24:1–24:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:1-John20:17\">JHN 20:1–20:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:11-Luke7:16\">LUK 7:11–7:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:38-John11:44\">JHN 11:38–11:44</a></p>\n<h2>The authority of Jesus Christ is seen in his teaching</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ claims authority for his own words</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:21-Matt5:22\">MAT 5:21–5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27-Matt5:28\">MAT 5:27–5:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:41-Matt12:42\">MAT 12:41–12:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:5\">MAT 17:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:7\">MRK 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:35\">LUK 9:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:5\">MRK 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:10\">MRK 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:15\">MRK 10:15</a> <em>The use of the phrase “I tell you the truth” emphasises Jesus Christ's authority</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26\">MRK 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:31\">MRK 13:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:24-John4:26\">JHN 4:24–4:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:15-John7:18\">JHN 7:15–7:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:48-John12:50\">JHN 12:48–12:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:13\">JHN 13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a> <em>The “I am” sayings in John's Gospel emphasise the divine nature of Jesus Christ's authority</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:3\">JHN 15:3</a></p>\n<h3>His authority is recognised by others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:28-Matt7:29\">MAT 7:28–7:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:33\">MAT 22:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:46\">MAT 22:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:22\">MRK 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:32\">LUK 4:32</a></p>\n<h3>His authority is questioned and opposed by others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:65-Matt26:68\">MAT 26:65–26:68</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:28-Luke4:30\">LUK 4:28–4:30</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ delegates his authority to others</h2>\n<h3>His followers preach in his name</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:7\">MAT 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:18–28:20</a></p>\n<h3>His followers continue his works</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1\">MAT 10:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7\">MRK 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1-Luke9:2\">LUK 9:1–9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:8\">MAT 10:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:15\">MRK 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:13\">MRK 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17-Mark16:18\">MRK 16:17–16:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:1-Luke10:12\">LUK 10:1–10:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:12\">JHN 14:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:6\">ACT 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:16\">ACT 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>His followers pronounce his forgiveness and judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:18\">MAT 18:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:11\">MRK 6:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:28-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:28–22:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:22-John20:23\">JHN 20:22–20:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:2-1Cor6:3\">1CO 6:2–6:3</a></p>\n<h2>The results of Jesus Christ's authority</h2>\n<h3>He receives honour and glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22-John5:23\">JHN 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:4\">JHN 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:5\">JHN 17:5</a></p>\n<h3>He arouses amazement</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:23\">MAT 12:23</a></p>\n<h3>He is opposed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:14\">MAT 12:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:6\">MRK 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:11\">LUK 6:11</a></p>\n<h3>He is feared</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:37\">LUK 8:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:34\">MAT 8:34</a></p>\n<h3>His disciples are opposed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16-Acts16:24\">ACT 16:16–16:24</a></p>\n<h2>The authority of the exalted Christ</h2>\n<h3>He is Lord</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:20\">EPH 1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>He is Lord of creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16-Col1:17\">COL 1:16–1:17</a></p>\n<h3>He is Lord of the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22\">EPH 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>He is judge</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a></p>\n<h3>He is Saviour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:15\">JHN 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:3\">JHN 14:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19-Col1:20\">COL 1:19–1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:13\">TIT 2:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:24-Heb7:25\">HEB 7:24–7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></p>\n<h3>He is interceder</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:25\">HEB 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:1\">1JN 2:1</a></p>",
